CSPP 51081
Lab 3, Ex 4 - my_sig

------
mystat
------

1. Run the makefile:
	prompt> make
	
2. Run the program:
	prompt> my_sig <number>
	
3. To clean up after:
	prompt> make clean 

------------	
What it does
------------
It takes a number from the command line, and assigns that number to
MAXSTOPS. It loops until you CTRL-C up to the number of MAXSTOPS.
With each loop, it waits, then trigger a SIGUSR1, which only
prints out that it has been handled.